-- Istanbul Commerce Chamber President Rejects Bribery Charges, Sabah Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2010-10-25T06:44:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/istanbul-commerce-chamber-president-rejects-bribery-charges-sabah-says.html
Murat Yalcintas, president of the
Istanbul Chamber of Commerce, remained in detention after
denying he ordered the bribery of legal professionals for land
deals,  Sabah  newspaper reported.  Yalcintas was one of more than 40 people, including lawyers
and top judges, detained by Turkish police last week in an
investigation into the alleged bribery ring, then released 14
after questioning, Sabah said. The probe relates to land deals
including the sale of Istanbulâ€™s World Trade Center and CNR
